problem_text: m \angle UOW = 50, and OV bisects \angle UOW. What is m \angle VOY?
proof:
Step 1:
Theorem: Known facts
Premises : start
Conclusions: ∠VOY, ∠AOU, BisectsAngle(OV, ∠WOU), ∠COE, ∠WOC, ∠UOA, ∠EOW, ∠YOA, ∠COD, ∠WOD, ∠AOC, ∠VOU, ∠WOU, W on AO, ∠COU, ∠AOD, V on CO, 3.14 = pi, ∠VOE, ∠EOA, Y on EO, ∠COY, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOU, ∠VOD, U on DO, ∠AOV, ∠YOV

Step 2:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠VOY
Conclusions: ∠VOY = 2 * pi - ∠YOV

Step 3:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠AOU
Conclusions: ∠AOU = 2 * pi - ∠UOA

Step 4:
Theorem: Bisects Angle Definition
Premises : BisectsAngle(OV, ∠WOU)
Conclusions: ∠VOU = ∠WOV

Step 5:
Theorem: Straight Angle
Premises : ∠WOU, ∠EOW
Conclusions: pi = ∠EOW + ∠WOU

Step 6:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠YOA, W on AO
Conclusions: ∠YOA = ∠YOW

Step 7:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠AOC, W on AO
Conclusions: ∠AOC = ∠WOC

Step 8:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : W on AO, ∠AOD
Conclusions: ∠AOD = ∠WOD

Step 9:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠COE, V on CO
Conclusions: ∠COE = ∠VOE

Step 10:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠COU, V on CO
Conclusions: ∠COU = ∠VOU

Step 11:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠AOC, V on CO
Conclusions: ∠AOC = ∠AOV

Step 12:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠WOC, V on CO
Conclusions: ∠WOC = ∠WOV

Step 13:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : V on CO, ∠COD
Conclusions: ∠COD = ∠VOD

Step 14:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠EOA, W on AO
Conclusions: ∠EOA = ∠EOW

Step 15:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : Y on EO, ∠EOA
Conclusions: ∠EOA = ∠YOA

Step 16:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : Y on EO, ∠COE
Conclusions: ∠COE = ∠COY

Step 17:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : V on CO, ∠COY
Conclusions: ∠COY = ∠VOY

Step 18:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠WOD, U on DO
Conclusions: ∠WOD = ∠WOU

Step 19:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠COD, U on DO
Conclusions: ∠COD = ∠COU

Step 20:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠AOD, U on DO
Conclusions: ∠AOD = ∠AOU

Step 21:
Theorem: Circumference splited
Premises : ∠VOU, ∠UOA, ∠AOV
Conclusions: 2 * pi = ∠AOV + ∠UOA + ∠VOU

Step 22:
Theorem: Circumference splited
Premises : ∠AOV, ∠EOA, ∠VOE
Conclusions: 2 * pi = ∠AOV + ∠EOA + ∠VOE

Step 23:
Theorem: Straight Angle
Premises : ∠VOU, ∠YOV
Conclusions: pi = ∠VOU + ∠YOV

Step 24:
Theorem: Straight Angle
Premises : ∠YOV, ∠VOD
Conclusions: pi = ∠VOD + ∠YOV

Step 25:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOC = ∠AOV, ∠AOC = ∠WOC
Conclusions: ∠AOV = ∠WOC

Step 26:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠EOA = ∠YOA, ∠YOA = ∠YOW
Conclusions: ∠EOA = ∠YOW

Step 27:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠COE = ∠COY, ∠COY = ∠VOY, ∠COE = ∠VOE
Conclusions: ∠VOE = ∠VOY

Step 28:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠WOD = ∠WOU, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOU
Conclusions: pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOD

Step 29:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠COD = ∠COU, ∠COD = ∠VOD
Conclusions: ∠COU = ∠VOD

Step 30:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOD = ∠WOD, ∠AOD = ∠AOU
Conclusions: ∠AOU = ∠WOD

Step 31:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi = ∠VOU + ∠YOV, 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: 3.14 = ∠VOU + ∠YOV

Step 32:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi = ∠VOD + ∠YOV, 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠YOV

Step 33:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠EOA = ∠EOW, ∠EOA = ∠YOW
Conclusions: ∠EOW = ∠YOW

Step 34:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠VOY = 2 * pi - ∠YOV, ∠VOE = ∠VOY
Conclusions: ∠VOE = 2 * pi - ∠YOV

Step 35:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠COU = ∠VOD, ∠COU = ∠VOU, ∠VOU = ∠WOV
Conclusions: ∠VOD = ∠WOV

Step 36:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOU = ∠WOD, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOD
Conclusions: pi * (50 / 180) = ∠AOU

Step 37:
Theorem: Substitution
Premises : ∠EOW = ∠YOW, pi = ∠EOW + ∠WOU, 3.14 = pi, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOU
Conclusions: 3.14 = pi * (50 / 180) + ∠YOW

Step 38:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠WOC = ∠WOV, ∠VOD = ∠WOV
Conclusions: ∠VOD = ∠WOC

Step 39:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOU = 2 * pi - ∠UOA, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠AOU
Conclusions: pi * (50 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠UOA

Step 40:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOV = ∠WOC, ∠VOD = ∠WOC
Conclusions: ∠AOV = ∠VOD

Step 41:
Theorem: Substitution
Premises : 2 * pi = ∠AOV + ∠EOA + ∠VOE, ∠AOV = ∠VOD, ∠EOA = ∠YOW, 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: 2 * 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠VOE + ∠YOW

Step 42:
Theorem: Solve Linear Equation System
Premises : 3.14 = pi * (50 / 180) + ∠YOW, pi * (50 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠UOA, 2 * 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠VOE + ∠YOW, ∠VOE = 2 * pi - ∠YOV, 2 * pi = ∠AOV + ∠UOA + ∠VOU, 3.14 = ∠VOU + ∠YOV, 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠YOV, ∠AOV = ∠VOD
Conclusions: 2.71 = ∠YOV
